      • SizedPriorityQueue

        public SizedPriorityQueue(int size,
                  boolean getLowest,
                  java.util.Comparator<T> comparator)
        Creates a fixed size priority queue with an explicit comparator for the class that you want to track. This can be handy if the generic class you have doesn't implement Comparable
        Parameters:
        size - - The maximum number of values to store
        getLowest - - false means to track the highest N values, true means to track the lowest N values
        comparator - - Explicit comparator for the class you are tracking
